The paper discusses a framework for accelerating CNN training on FPGA clusters, which involves distributed computing, parallelism, and optimization of workload and weight partitioning. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Architecture (cs.AR), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
